Only mail hours other than that standard ;S within a node's zone should be given. Since ;S observance of mail hour within one's zone is ;S mandatory, it should not be indicated. ;S ;S ;S The following flag defines user-specific values. If present, this ;S flag MUST be the last flag present in a nodelist entry. ;S ;S Flag Meaning ;S ;S ;S Ux..x ;S A user-specified string, which may contain any ;S alphanumeric character except blanks. This string may ;S contain one to thirty-two characters of information that ;S may be used to add user-defined data to a specific ;S nodelist entry. The character "U" should NOT be ;S repeated, eg, ",UXXX,YYY,ZZZ" not ",UXXX,UYYY,UZZZ". ;S ;S It is recommended that the initial "U" is not followed by ;S a comma and that flags following the first entry be ;S separated by a comma, as in the above example. ;S ;S Entries following the "U" flag must be of a technical or ;S administrative nature. Not more than one entry ;S in the zone 1 segment may carry this flag and that entry ;S must be the current Zone EchoMail Coordinator. ;S ;S REC Regional EchoMail Coordinator. Not more than one ;S entry in any region may carry this flag and that entry ;S must be the current Regional EchoMail Coordinator. ;S ;S NEC Network EchoMail coordinator. Not more than one entry ;S in any net may carry this flag and that entry must be the ;S current Network EchoMail Coordinator of that Net. ;S ;S ;S Other User Flags Currently Authorized for use in Zone 1: ;S ;S Z19 Zyxel 19,200 modem protocol ;S ;S ;S ISDN connected nodes: ;S ;S ISDNA 19200 N81, ITU-T V.110/ECMA 102, Hayes compatible, ISDN only ;S ISDNB 38400 N81, ITU-T V.110/ECMA 102, Hayes compatible, ISDN only ;S ISDNC 64000, ISDN Common API, X.75, ISDN only ;S ;S Technical restrictions: ;S ;S ITU-T V.110 is a Modem emulation with implementation of connect ;S requests via Hayes command set or V.25.bis. As the Hayes AT ;S command set is used on analog connections, it is recommended for ;S use on ISDN connections as well. ;S ;S For ALL 3 flags, the following restrictions apply: ;S ;S ONLY nodes with the SAME FLAG may CONNECT with each other. This is ;S due to the fact that under ISDN, auto-baud detect is not possible ;S and CAPI applications currently cannot connect using V.110 modem ;S emulation. ;S ;S Nodes using these flags should use a modem "speed" of 300 baud. ;S This is due to limitations imposed by nodelist processing software. ;S ;S Nodelist entries would look (perhaps) like this: ;S ;S ,34,Deti's_BBS,Dortmund,Detlef_Koester,99-999-1234567,300,UISDNA ;S ,34,Deti's_BBS,Dortmund,Detlef_Koester,99-999-2345678,300,UISDNB ;S ,34,Deti's_BBS,Dortmund,Detlef_Koester,99-999-3456789,300,UISDNC ;S ;S ==========================================================================
